obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (87356)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 10th May, 2024, Vide notification No. S.R.O. 13(E), dated 08th May, 2024, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87356&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Inter-services Organisations`
  line `(Command, Control and Discipline) Act, 2023.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (87357)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87357&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall apply to all persons who are subject to the Air`
  line `Force Act, 1950, (45 of 1950), the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950) and the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957), and`
  line `to persons of such other forces as the Central Government may specify, by notification, under section 4,`
  line `who are serving in or attached to an Inter-services Organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (87358)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87358&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "Air Officer" means any officer of the Air Force above the rank of group captain;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chief of Defence Staff" means an officer of the regular Army, or the Indian Navy, or the Air`
  line `Force, as the case may be, appointed as such by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) "Commander-in-Chief" means a General Officer of the regular Army, or a Flag Officer of the`
  line `Indian Navy, or an Air Officer of the Air Force, appointed as Commander-in-Chief of a Joint Services`
  line `Command, and in his absence, the officer on whom the command devolves;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commanding Officer" means the officer in actual command of the unit, ship or establishment`
  line `and includes an officer appointed as such by the Commander-in-Chief or the Officer-in-Command, as`
  line `the case may be, of an Inter-services Organisation;`
  line
  line `(e) "Flag Officer" means an officer of the rank of Admiral of the Fleet, Admiral, Vice-Admiral or`
  line Rear-Admiral;
  line
  line `(f) "General Officer" means an officer of the regular Army above the rank of Brigadier;`
  line
  line `(g) "Inter-services Organisation" means a body of troops including a Joint Services Command`
  line `consisting of persons, subject to the Air Force Act, 1950, (45 of 1950), the Army Act, 1950 (46 of`
  line `1950)and the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957) or any two of the said Acts;`
  line
  line `(h)"notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i)"officer", in relation to an Inter-services Organisation, means an officer as defined in`
  line `clause (xxiii) of section 4 of the Air Force Act, 1950, (45 of 1950), or clause (xviii) of section 3 of the`
  line `Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), or clause (16) of section 3 of the Navy Act, 1957, (62 of 1957) as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(j) "Officer-in-Command" of an Inter-services Organisation means either a General Officer of the`
  line `regular Army, or a Flag Officer of the Indian Navy, or an Air Officer of the Air Force, appointed as the`
  line `Officer-in-Command of an Inter-services Organisation, other than Joint Services Command, and in his`
  line `absence, the officer on whom the command devolves;`
  line
  line `(k)"regulations" means the regulations made under the respective Service Acts;`
  line
  line `(l) "rules" means the rules made under this Act and under the respective Service Acts, as the case`
  line `may be;`
  line
  line `(m) "Service Acts" means the Air Force Act, 1950, (45 of 1950), or the Army Act, 1950 (46 of`
  line `1950), or the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957) or any two of the said Acts or all the said Acts; and`
  line
  line `(n) "service personnel" means persons who are subject to any of the Service Acts.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Air Force Act, 1950,`
  line `(45 of 1950), or the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), or the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957)shall have the`
  line `meanings, respectively, assigned to them under the said Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (87359)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Special provision for certain forces under Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87359&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, specify any force or any part thereof, raised and maintained in India under the authority`
  line `of the said Government, to which all or any of the provisions of this Act shall, with or without modifications,`
  line `apply and accordingly all the officers referred to in clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 3 shall be deemed`
  line `to be officers within the meaning of the respective Acts relating to the said forces.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon issuance of a notification under sub-section (1), the authority to exercise all the disciplinary`
  line `and administrative powers under the respective Acts governing such force or any part thereof including the`
  line `powers conferred by warrants or commissions issued under such Acts governing that force or any part`
  line `thereof, shall vest in the Commander-in-Chief or the Officer-in-Command, as the case may be, of the Interservices Organisation.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any of the provisions of this Act applies to a force or any part thereof as referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2), the Central Government may, by notification, direct that by what authority or which officer,`
  line `the jurisdiction, powers or duties incidental to the operation of the provisions of this Act shall be exercised`
  line `or performed in respect of that force or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (87360)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Inter- services Organisation or Joint Services Command.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87360&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, constitute an Inter-services Organisation, which may include a Joint`
  line `Services Command, comprising of units or service personnel who are subject to any of the Service Acts, as`
  line `may be placed under the command of the Commander-in-Chief or, as the case may be, the Officer-inCommand.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by an order published in the Official Gazette, direct that any power`
  line `exercisable by the Commander-in-Chief or, as the case may be, the Officer-in-Command may also be`
  line `exercisable by any other officer specially empowered in this behalf by the said Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (87374)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Existing Inter-services Organisations and Commander-in-Chief or Officer-in-Command to continue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87374&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) the Inter-services Organisations constituted by the Central Government and functioning as such`
  line `immediately before the date of commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to have been constituted`
  line `under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the Commander-in-Chief or, as the case may be, the Officer-in-Command of an Inter-services`
  line `Organisation, who has been appointed and functioning as such immediately before the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to have been appointed under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Act shall render invalid any action taken or acts performed, immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act, by the Inter-services Organisation, or by the Commander-in-Chief`
  line `or by the Officer-in-Command, as the case may be, of an Inter-services Organisation, while functioning as`
  line `such under any law applicable at that time.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (87362)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers of Commander- in-Chief or Officer-in-Command.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87362&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commander-in-Chief or, as`
  line `the case may be, Officer-in-Command of an Inter-services Organisation, shall be the head of such Interservices Organisation and shall exercise command and control over the personnel serving in or attached to`
  line `that Inter-services Organisation, for the purpose of maintenance of discipline and proper discharge of their`
  line duties.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Commander-in-Chief or, as the case may be, the Officerin-Command of an Inter-services Organisation shall be competent to exercise all the disciplinary and`
  line `administrative powers vested in and exercised by—`
  line
  line `(a) the General Officer Commanding the Army;`
  line
  line `(b) the Flag Officer Commanding-in-Chief of a Naval Command;`
  line
  line `(c) the Air Officer Commanding-in-Chief of an Air Command;`
  line
  line `(d) any other officer or authority specified in the Service Acts or in the rules and regulations made`
  line `thereunder, including the powers conferred by warrants or commissions issued under the provisions of`
  line `such Service Acts; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other officer or authority as may be specified in the notification issued under section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (87363)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Commanding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87363&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Commanding Officer of an Inter-services Organisation shall, in`
  line `addition to having command over any unit, ship or establishment, also perform such duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him in respect of such Inter-services Organisation by its Commander-in-Chief or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Officer-in-Command and shall be empowered to initiate all disciplinary or administrative`
  line `actions over the personnel appointed, deputed, posted or attached to that Inter-services Organisation.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (87364)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Superintendence of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87364&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The superintendence of the Inter-services`
  line `Organisation shall vest in the Central Government, which shall have the power to issue directions to each`
  line `of such organisations, on any matters concerning national security or general administration, if it considers`
  line `necessary and expedient so to do in the public interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (87365)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to declare persons to be on active service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87365&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Service Acts, the Central Government may, by notification, declare that any service personnel or class of`
  line `service personnel to whom the Service Acts apply shall, with reference to any Inter-services Organisation`
  line `in which he or they may be serving in or attached to or with reference to any provision of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to be on active service within the meaning of this Act and the Service Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (87366)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87366&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make rules for the purposes of carrying out`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (87367)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Overriding effect of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87367&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (87368)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87368&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or any other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (87369)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87369&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (87370)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Laying of rules before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253&sectionId=87370&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_1408_00016_202328_1715339556253
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for`
  line `a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions,`
  line `and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in such rule or both Houses agree that the rule`
  line `should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as`
  line `the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
